hout compromising the Si\npassivation quality. The Si resilience decreased as AIGSe > CGSe > CZTS, in\naccordance with the measured Cu contamination profiles and higher annealing\ntemperatures. An efficiency of up to 7% was achieved for a CZTS/Si tandem,\nwhere the Si bottom cell is no longer the limiting factor.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 4 Nov 2021 16:25:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-11-05"}
