 be responsible for\nthe observed correlation between the radio and $\\gamma$-ray variability. We\npresent a scenario that connects the positive correlation and the unusual\nanti-correlation by combining the production of a flare and a dip at\n$\\gamma$-rays by a strong moving shock at different distances from the jet\napex.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 4 Nov 2021 17:05:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-02-02"}
