cific risk evaluation suggested the highest-risk\noccupations were registered nurses, medical assistants, and respiratory\ntherapists, with estimated risks of 0.0189, 0.0188, and 0.0176, respectively.\nTo validate the population-level risk model, the infection risk in Texas and\nCalifornia was estimated. The proposed model will significantly influence the\nPPE allocation and safety plans for HCP\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 5 Nov 2021 01:02:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-11-11"}
